             was indicted for <rs id="t18280911-266-off1365" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18280911-266-off1365" type="offenceCategory" value="theft"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280911-266-off1365" type="offenceSubcategory" value="pocketpicking"></interp>
               stealing, on the <rs id="t18280911-266-cd1366" type="crimeDate">1st of August</rs>
                     <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t18280911-266-off1365 t18280911-266-cd1366"></join>, 1 watch, value 4l., 1 seal, value 6d., and 1 key, value 1d., the good of 
                     <persName id="t18280911-266-victim1478" type="victimName">
                        William 
                        Gray
                     <interp inst="t18280911-266-victim1478" type="surname" value="Gray"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18280911-266-victim1478" type="given" value="William"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18280911-266-victim1478" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t18280911-266-off1365 t18280911-266-victim1478"></join>
                     </persName>
                  , from his person
            </rs>.</p>
               <p>WILLIAM GRAY. I am a <rs id="t18280911-266-viclabel1367" type="occupation">ship-carpenter</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18280911-266-victim1478 t18280911-266-viclabel1367"></join>. On the 1st of August I was standing at the end of <placeName id="t18280911-266-crimeloc1368">Field-alley, Shadwell-market</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18280911-266-crimeloc1368" type="placeName" value="Field-alley, Shadwell-market"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18280911-266-crimeloc1368" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18280911-266-off1365 t18280911-266-crimeloc1368"></join>, speaking to a ship-mate; I found the prisoner before me, who said some words which were unintelligible - he then made a grasp and took my watch; I seized him, but he got away - we pursued, and about fifteen yards before we came up with him, I heard something fall on the ground; we did not stop, but pursued and took him - we brought him back to where I heard something fall, and it was my watch.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18280911-266-person1479">
                  JOHN 
                  SKUES
               <interp inst="t18280911-266-person1479" type="surname" value="SKUES"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280911-266-person1479" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280911-266-person1479" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a watchman. On the morning of the 1st of August I took the prisoner from Gray; he took me to the place, and there was this watch, I saw it picked up.(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I was coming up Cox's-lane, and heard a cry of Stop thief! this person caught hold of me.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t18280911-266-verdict1369" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18280911-266-verdict1369" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
               GUILTY
            </rs>. Aged 22.</p>
